<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 3:46PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
south central Roanoke, northeastern Floyd, western Franklin and
southeastern Montgomery Counties through 430 PM EDT...
At 346 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pilot, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Christiansburg...
Pilot...
Copper Hill...
Bent Mountain...
Ferrum...
Terrys Fork...
and Check.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
